SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 69, Chapter 9, Part 2, is amended by
adding the following as new sections:
69-9-229.
(a)
(1) Commercial paddle craft operators who use agency boat ramps are
required to pay to the agency a fee of forty-two cents (42Â¢) each time a
nonmotorized vessel controlled by a commercial paddle craft operation utilizes
an agency boat ramp.
(2) Each use of an agency boat ramp to launch a nonmotorized vessel
into the water, remove the vessel from the water, or both as part of a single trip
constitutes a single occurrence for the purpose of imposing the fee prescribed in
subdivision (a)(1).
(3) Commercial paddle craft operators who pay the fee prescribed in
subdivision (a)(1) shall receive parking lot passes issued by the agency in the
form of stickers to be applied prominently on vehicles and trailers for the use of
agency ramps for unloading, loading, and conducting general business
operations.
(4) This subsection (a) does not apply to commercial paddle craft
operators using agency boat ramps on the Ocoee River.
(b)
